            <title>[SPARK-19531] History server doesn&apos;t refresh jobs for long-life apps like thriftserver</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-19531</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If spark.history.fs.logDirectory points to hdfs, then spark history server doesn&apos;t refresh jobs page. This is caused by Hadoop - during writing to the .inprogress file Hadoop doesn&apos;t update file length until close and therefor Spark&apos;s history server is not able to detect any changes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m gonna submit a PR to fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
